This paper discusses the network investigation of a file synchronisation service, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also outlines a methodology for retrieving digital evidence from the network, which involves aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC), network infrastructure (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), and cybercrime (cs.CY).
